Your once quiet town is being flooded with refugees, speaking tales of unspeakable horror from their now desolate towns and villages. Murders, beasts of the night, curses and all manor of ill. It becomes clear that werewolves will soon be descending on your village. Many of your peers have packed up and left, not wishing to stick around to see what may become of this place and taking with them almost all items of value.

Those that remain in the village have a huge distrust for each other, with rumours not just of rival gangs, but also individuals locked in blood feuds. There has also been tales of a vengeful poltergeist haunting the village, feeding off the sorrow and despair of the refugees that flood in, although such things are hard to prove. To make matters worse, the sheriff found what appears to be elaborate suicide plans from an insane individual who is intent on 'going out with a bang'.

Those of you that have stayed, how vowed to defend the village from the incoming onslaught, and whilst you prepare for the potential of werewolves, you also get the feeling that foul magics are in the air and this isn't going to be a straightforward battle.

Tormented in life by your peers in the village, you saught help and solace with the local coven. Your misplaced trust led to you being held captave, your flesh torn, hair burned, tears harvested in endless torment. One day you manage to free yourself during a conflict between the coven and some unknown beasts. Running for hours you eventually come across a stranger who claims to have also been held captive by the coven, you decide to camp together for safety under the bright sky of the full moon. That night, you witness a horrific change in your new companion, and there is no where to run. The last thing you remember is feeling the softness of their fur as their teeth sink into your neck. In your final breath you curse all those who walk this land.
Your thirst for vengence is preventing you from passing into the next life. You will not be able to rest until you have taken your revenge and felt the life slip away from those who wronged you.
Objective: Become lynched whilst possessing exactly 1 village, 1 coven and 1 werewolf. You can possess a maximum of 6 times.

Unable to sleep due to horrific nightmares about the torment to come. If it's not wolves tearing into your flesh, it's witches poisoning your porridge, or the village turning on each other. You had ideas to help save everyone, but no one cares about you in this town, most of them don't even know your name. Your attempts to help have been scoffed at, and your ideas mocked. So instead you will make them fear you! You've heard about these types of attacks from other villages, and most here are going to die anyway. So why not go out with a bang? Every day you strap some dynamite under your garments, and hope to be lead to the stake and burned. If you are going down, it's going to be the most spectacular and memorable lynching in history. Then all those idiots will remember your name forever!
Objective: Get lynched with a 2/3 majority. All visible votes count including votes that would otherwise not usually count towards the total.
*Upon getting lynched, a random person in the crowd will be impaled by debris from your exploding corpse, and die that night from sepsis. (from those who voted to lynch you)

A former upstanding member of a loving family and thriving village, you have managed to shake certain elements of the curse of the wolf and regained some semblance of your sanity and morality. You roam from village to village seeking to find the militia who failed to protect you and your family the night you were cursed with this horrible affliciton. Your search has led you to this village, and you are sure they are here somewhere. You will have your vengeance!
Alternative win-condition: Kill the Militia who wronged you before they kill you. Then finally take your rest.

A sole survivor of previous werewolf attacks from another village long ago, you are filled with great shame for abandoning your post and fleeing, leaving countless innocent to die. You have recently settled down in this new village when rumours of werewolf attacks have started up again. Tired of running from village to village you join the local militia to put your experience to good use. Telling yourself 'this time, I will stand strong'.

In the early hours of the morning you tracked a werewolf to the house of a family. Strangely this wolf ignored the family and took some of their livestock instead. Tracking the blood you are shocked to find the werewolf feasting. It howls your name in anger as it tears into the flesh of it's victim. Luckily you are not spotted and you watch as it runs off into the night.
Alternative win condition: Kill the Maple-Wolf that is hunting you and flee the village before others arrive.

Obviously, you would need to make sure the recruit couldn't just sell out the whole team, and you would probably need to either incentivize staying with the recruit or making the "leave" option less nice.
